1
00:00:58,025 --> 00:00:59,390
In the mid-18th century,

2
00:00:59,626 --> 00:01:00,787
the people of Taiwan
was dragged into

3
00:01:01,028 --> 00:01:02,393
imperialism from
both the East and the West.

4
00:01:02,629 --> 00:01:04,597
The conflict in Asia began with

5
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:07,994
the Opium War in 1840.

6
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:08,963
International battles such as
the Mutan Village Incident

7
00:01:09,202 --> 00:01:11,534
and the Sino-French War

8
00:01:11,772 --> 00:01:13,797
took place in Taiwan in succession.

9
00:01:14,308 --> 00:01:15,742
In 1885,

10
00:01:15,976 --> 00:01:18,707
the Qing government decided
to make Taiwan a province

11
00:01:18,979 --> 00:01:20,310
and appointed Liu Ming-Chuan

12
00:01:20,547 --> 00:01:22,606
its first governor.

13
00:01:23,050 --> 00:01:23,812
Liu also wanted to

14
00:01:24,051 --> 00:01:26,748
modernize Taiwan.

15
00:01:27,154 --> 00:01:28,212
But ten years later, Japan
defeated the Qing government

16
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:31,823
in the First Sino-Japanese War.

17
00:01:32,059 --> 00:01:33,618
In the end, Liu gave up this island

18
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:36,124
situated at the outskirts
of the Qing Empire.

19
00:01:37,164 --> 00:01:38,154
Then the Japanese

20
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:40,526
with the arrogance of conquerors,

21
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:41,757
arrived at their first

22
00:01:42,002 --> 00:01:44,130
colony overseas.

23
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:46,562
What they didn't expect was

24
00:01:46,807 --> 00:01:49,435
the fierce resistance
from the islanders,

25
00:01:49,676 --> 00:01:51,508
whose courage and endurance

26
00:01:51,745 --> 00:01:54,043
far exceeded those of the Qing army.

27
00:02:14,668 --> 00:02:23,076
If you want to know more
about Taiwan,

28
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:40,288
the Treaty of Shimonoseki
will tell you all.

29
00:02:44,364 --> 00:02:49,200
Japan's weapons

30
00:02:55,442 --> 00:02:56,568
After the Meiji Restoration

31
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,744
at the end of the 19th century,

32
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:01,913
Japan had become
a modernized country.

33
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:04,550
It began to use arms
to increase its influence.

34
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:07,152
But the Qing Empire
didn't want to lose

35
00:03:07,387 --> 00:03:10,379
its position as the suzerain
of East Asian countries.

36
00:03:10,724 --> 00:03:12,488
Thus, in 1894,

37
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:13,716
the interference of
these two countries in

38
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,928
the internal affairs of Korea

39
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:18,461
resulted in
the First Sino-Japanese War.

40
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:20,133
As the Qing government
lost the war,

41
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:21,766
the Treaty of Shimonoseki
was signed.

42
00:03:22,002 --> 00:03:22,662
The fate of Taiwan

43
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:25,199
was how in the hands of
the rising Japanese Empire.

44
00:03:33,346 --> 00:03:35,405
On April 17, 1895,

45
00:03:35,649 --> 00:03:37,777
a rumor got around in Taipei

46
00:03:38,018 --> 00:03:40,487
that Li Hong-Zhang
had signed a peace treaty

47
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:42,746
with Prime Minister
Ito Hirobumi in Japan

48
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:44,684
and that the Qing Empire had ceded

49
00:03:44,991 --> 00:03:46,652
Taiwan and Penghu to Japan.

50
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,292
Once the news was spread,

51
00:03:48,528 --> 00:03:49,393
the people of Taiwan,

52
00:03:49,629 --> 00:03:51,757
especially government officials,
wealthy merchants,

53
00:03:51,998 --> 00:03:53,591
landowners, and intellectuals,

54
00:03:53,834 --> 00:03:56,496
were shocked, angered and worried.

55
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:04,910
Although the Treaty of
Shimonoseki stated that

56
00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:07,479
Japan could take
the Liaodong Peninsula,

57
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:10,775
intervention by Russia,
Germany and France

58
00:04:11,017 --> 00:04:11,916
forced the Japanese government

59
00:04:12,152 --> 00:04:14,553
to give up that already secured asset.

60
00:04:14,821 --> 00:04:17,313
This turnout gave hope

61
00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:19,150
to people who did not wish

62
00:04:19,392 --> 00:04:21,224
to see Taiwan in Japan's hands.

63
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:26,126
Tang Ching-Sung,
the governor of Taiwan,

64
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:28,061
was hinted by the Qing government

65
00:04:28,301 --> 00:04:30,736
to use international law
and public opinion

66
00:04:30,971 --> 00:04:32,996
to stop the cession of Taiwan.

67
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,504
Therefore, men such as

68
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:37,506
Chiu Feng-Chia, Lin Chao-Tong

69
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:38,836
and Lin Wei-Yuan
successively joined

70
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:41,844
the cause to establish
The Taiwan Republic.

71
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:56,553
Meat buns...

72
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:57,662
Delicious meat buns...

73
00:04:57,898 --> 00:04:58,797
At the end of the 19th century,

74
00:04:59,032 --> 00:05:01,126
Taiwan had a population
about three million.

75
00:05:01,368 --> 00:05:03,462
Most of them are descendents
from Zhangzhou and Quanzhou

76
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:05,899
of the Fujian areas and
of the Hakka immigrants.

77
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:07,363
The government officials serving
in Taiwan

78
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:10,201
were appointed
by the emperor in Beijing.

79
00:05:11,545 --> 00:05:12,341
You have great taste.

80
00:05:12,579 --> 00:05:14,206
This fabric would be tailored
into a beautiful robe.

81
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:15,945
Oh, it's not for clothing.

82
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,674
At that time,

83
00:05:17,951 --> 00:05:20,181
silver and bronze coins were used
in trade,

84
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,548
and agriculture was the base of life.

85
00:05:22,789 --> 00:05:23,915
Compared to Japan
and modernized countries

86
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:25,922
in Europe and America,

87
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,526
Taiwan was still a closed society.

88
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:34,632
Thank you.

89
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:35,733
Watch your step.

90
00:06:16,676 --> 00:06:18,735
We no longer know who designed

91
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:20,310
the flag of the Taiwan Republic.

92
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:21,604
Since The Taiwan Republic

93
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:23,816
still supported the Qing Empire,

94
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,917
whose flag featured a dragon,

95
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,817
a tiger was chosen instead.

96
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:07,022
The Taiwan Republic is claimed to be

97
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,194
the first republic in Asia.

98
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:11,323
Its reign title is Yongqing,

99
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:14,056
meaning always belonging
to the Qing Empire.

100
00:07:14,301 --> 00:07:16,201
President Tang Ching-Sung
even declared

101
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,598
The Taiwan Republic would
shield the Qing Dynasty.

102
00:07:19,739 --> 00:07:21,969
Yet, how did the people of Taiwan

103
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:23,903
look at The Taiwan Republic?

104
00:07:24,678 --> 00:07:25,611
This was how Davidson,

105
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:27,142
an American reporter in Taipei

106
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:28,939
at that time, described it.

107
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:32,812
I expected that the memorable day
would find the streets filled

108
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:36,421
with holidaymakers arrayed
in their best clothes.

109
00:07:36,656 --> 00:07:39,125
The houses gay with flags,

110
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:41,987
and the day noisy with firecrackers.

111
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:43,923
But it was not so.

112
00:07:44,097 --> 00:07:47,192
All things jogged along as usual.

113
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:49,528
The pretty tea girls picked their tea

114
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:52,503
no with addition to their all time
coquettishness,

115
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:56,141
and the tea box makers and painters
worked along

116
00:07:56,242 --> 00:07:58,301
in their usual busy style.

117
00:07:58,778 --> 00:08:02,408
Not a new flag or firecracker
in the settlement.

118
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:06,316
On this day,

119
00:08:06,553 --> 00:08:08,715
an official seal was cast,

120
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:11,890
Tang Ching-Sung was nominated as
president of The Taiwan Republic and

121
00:08:12,092 --> 00:08:15,221
Liu Yung-Fu as brigadier general
of Tainan.

122
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:19,527
Tang knelt down twice and
kowtowed six times to

123
00:08:19,766 --> 00:08:22,497
receive the seal,
but the Japanese Navy was approaching

124
00:08:22,736 --> 00:08:23,931
and the situation was tense,

125
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,798
so the unfinished ceremony

126
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,065
was postponed until
the following day.

127
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:31,243
After 21-gun salute,

128
00:08:31,478 --> 00:08:33,742
the blue flag with a yellow tiger

129
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:36,108
of the Taiwan Republic was hung.

130
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:38,908
But when the flag was raised,

131
00:08:39,119 --> 00:08:41,019
it started to pour.

132
00:08:41,388 --> 00:08:44,517
The tiger,
painted on with yellow chalk,

133
00:08:44,758 --> 00:08:47,693
was washed off.

134
00:08:47,961 --> 00:08:50,191
This seemed to foreshadow

135
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:53,092
the future of the Taiwan Republic

136
00:09:19,692 --> 00:09:22,059
On May 31, 1895,
Japanese troops landed

137
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:25,492
on Yenliao
on Taiwan's Northeast Coast.

138
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:26,722
On June 2nd,

139
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:29,094
Li Jing-Fang,
the son of Li Hong-Zhang,

140
00:09:29,335 --> 00:09:32,600
handed Taiwan over
to Japanese representative

141
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:36,469
Kabayama Sukenori on
a ship outside of Keelung.

142
00:09:43,983 --> 00:09:44,916
On June 3rd,

143
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:47,314
Japanese troops surrounded
Keelung on land and sea.

144
00:11:23,383 --> 00:11:24,475
The Regular Army of
the Qing government

145
00:11:24,717 --> 00:11:27,311
was defeated
at Shihchiuling, Keelung.

146
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:30,513
The defeated soldiers
rushed into Taipei,

147
00:11:30,757 --> 00:11:32,156
set fire and pillaged the city.

148
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:07,250
On the evening of June 4th,

149
00:12:07,493 --> 00:12:08,392
Tang Ching-Sung abandoned

150
00:12:08,628 --> 00:12:11,359
the 10-day old Taiwan Republic

151
00:12:11,598 --> 00:12:14,590
and boarded a German ship
back to Xiamen.

152
00:12:26,546 --> 00:12:27,604
After Tang left,

153
00:12:27,847 --> 00:12:29,941
Taipei went into chaos.

154
00:12:30,149 --> 00:12:30,945
Local and foreign merchants

155
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,244
living in Taipei hoped the

156
00:12:33,486 --> 00:12:36,217
Japanese army would soon
arrive to restore order.

157
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:37,218
So they delegated Koo Hsien-Jung,

158
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:40,722
a general store owner,

159
00:12:40,994 --> 00:12:42,484
to meet with the Japanese
in Keelung

160
00:12:42,729 --> 00:12:44,254
and to ask them to enter the city.

161
00:12:56,876 --> 00:12:58,037
On June 17,

162
00:12:58,278 --> 00:12:59,905
General Kabayama Sukenori
of Japan

163
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:02,444
at Taiwan Provincial
Administration Hall in Taipei

164
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:04,275
held a commencement ceremony

165
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:07,746
and became the first Japanese
Governor-General to Taiwan.

166
00:13:08,187 --> 00:13:09,177
With that, Japan officially won

167
00:13:09,422 --> 00:13:11,390
its first overseas colony.

168
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:12,784
After the ceremony,

169
00:13:13,026 --> 00:13:14,926
Japanese troops began to move south,

170
00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:17,927
preparing for the take-over.

171
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,665
American reporter Davidson

172
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:28,031
described the take-over process

173
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:30,072
as follows:

174
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:35,073
Since Taiwan was already
taken by a treaty,

175
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,048
the Japanese mistakenly believe

176
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:40,518
that establishing themselves upon
the island would be a simple matter.

177
00:13:40,753 --> 00:13:43,120
They never suspected that campaign
would prove

178
00:13:43,189 --> 00:13:46,318
even more arduous than
the north China conflict

179
00:13:46,426 --> 00:13:48,520
by which they had won it.

180
00:14:51,491 --> 00:14:53,084
When Japanese soldiers crossed
the Tamsui River

181
00:14:53,326 --> 00:14:54,953
into Taoyuan, Hsinchu
and Miaoli areas,

182
00:14:55,161 --> 00:14:56,356
they were welcomed
by smiling civilians

183
00:14:56,596 --> 00:14:58,428
waving white flags.

184
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:00,665
However,
few soldiers who fell behind

185
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:03,664
often got attacked by militiamen.

186
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:10,206
Fire!

187
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:13,374
While the Japanese troops
moved south,

188
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,411
some groups of heavily armed men

189
00:15:15,648 --> 00:15:17,582
who wanted to protect
their homesteads,

190
00:15:17,817 --> 00:15:19,546
making use of
topographical advantages,

191
00:15:19,786 --> 00:15:21,914
fought a guerilla warfare
with these intruders.

192
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:24,380
The Japanese couldn't distinguish

193
00:15:24,624 --> 00:15:26,251
the civilians from the rebels.

194
00:15:26,492 --> 00:15:28,984
So Taoyuan and East Hsinchu,

195
00:15:29,228 --> 00:15:31,390
were swept down
without discrimination.

196
00:15:31,697 --> 00:15:32,459
But it brought the contrary effect.

197
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:33,130
It drove people

198
00:15:33,366 --> 00:15:35,164
who weren't anti-Japanese activists

199
00:15:35,401 --> 00:15:37,267
to join the rebels.

200
00:17:03,055 --> 00:17:05,615
When the Japanese entered Taipei,

201
00:17:05,925 --> 00:17:08,519
the highly esteemed scholar
Wu Te-Kung from Changhua

202
00:17:08,761 --> 00:17:10,889
was invited by the magistrate
of Taiwan county

203
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:12,894
to discuss details of
resistance to the Japanese.

204
00:17:13,299 --> 00:17:15,461
Besides recruiting local
warriors and grouping them

205
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,693
Wu also collected funds
from community members

206
00:17:18,938 --> 00:17:21,032
to keep the group going.

207
00:17:48,134 --> 00:17:51,434
I heard local gents and
leaders in Taoyuan, Hsinchu

208
00:17:51,671 --> 00:17:55,471
and Miaoli like Wu Tang-Hsin,
Chiang Shao-Chu,

209
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:58,837
Huang Nan-Chiu, and Hsu Shiang

210
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:02,007
led warriors against the Japanese.

211
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:05,980
I admire their courage and strength,

212
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:10,655
but what worries me now

213
00:18:12,992 --> 00:18:14,892
is my men.

214
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:16,492
They can hold up against

215
00:18:16,729 --> 00:18:18,254
a disorderly group of bandits.

216
00:18:19,231 --> 00:18:21,495
But regarding

217
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:24,431
Japanese troops with modern arms,

218
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,999
I don't think my people
can fight against them.

219
00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:50,759
The Japanese continued to
call for reinforcements

220
00:18:50,997 --> 00:18:52,931
to drive the rebels in Taoyuan,

221
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,361
Hsinchu and Miaoli southward.

222
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,125
Finally,
a large-scale fighting broke out

223
00:18:56,369 --> 00:18:58,235
in Baguan Mountain area.

224
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:00,335
The anti-Japanese militants

225
00:19:00,573 --> 00:19:02,735
were almost wiped out

226
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,704
at this battle.

227
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,327
Hold.

228
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:29,762
They're out.

229
00:19:31,937 --> 00:19:33,200
Hold.

230
00:19:34,774 --> 00:19:35,764
Fire!

231
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:21,047
When I got back to the city,

232
00:20:21,353 --> 00:20:24,254
90% of the houses were empty.

233
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:25,980
Trees and plants withered

234
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,818
and streets were deserted.

235
00:20:28,527 --> 00:20:33,089
Many women lost their
husbands and sons.

236
00:20:34,366 --> 00:20:36,164
An epidemic was going around.

237
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,302
Life was even harder.

238
00:20:39,472 --> 00:20:42,601
Being desperate,

239
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:48,813
1 only asked for a life of peace
with my family.

240
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,165
Being stationed in Tainan,
Liu Yung-Fu, the leader

241
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,529
of the Black Flags,
didn't send reinforcements

242
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:14,604
to fight the Japanese in
Northern and Central Taiwan

243
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:17,172
Instead, taking advantage of
the raging battle,

244
00:21:17,409 --> 00:21:20,208
he founded
the Taiwan Republic in Tainan

245
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:21,936
to reorganize defense forces
and to wait for

246
00:21:22,181 --> 00:21:24,513
the Qing government
to send reinforcements.

247
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:26,818
The Black Flags are coming...

248
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:28,850
The Black Flags are coming...

249
00:21:29,088 --> 00:21:31,022
The Black Flags are coming...

250
00:21:31,257 --> 00:21:33,157
The Black Flags re coming...

251
00:21:33,392 --> 00:21:34,723
The Black Flags are coming...

252
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:15,699
In October 1895,

253
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:17,436
Japanese troops approached Tainan.

254
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:19,661
Liu knew he could not fight them.

255
00:22:19,972 --> 00:22:21,406
Following
Tang Ching-Sung's footsteps

256
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,937
he went back to China.

257
00:22:23,209 --> 00:22:23,835
At this time,

258
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:27,011
the Qing government retreated
completely from Taiwan.

259
00:22:50,803 --> 00:23:00,577
Japan had many weapons.

260
00:23:00,813 --> 00:23:08,982
They fought from Taipei to Tainan.

261
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:16,493
Black Flags were against
White Flags.

262
00:23:18,197 --> 00:23:21,929
The people of Taiwan were scared.

263
00:23:22,134 --> 00:23:25,695
To protect their lives,

264
00:23:25,971 --> 00:23:33,037
they stayed at home.

265
00:23:35,547 --> 00:23:42,283
One had better prepare
black flags and white flags.

266
00:23:42,521 --> 00:23:47,391
It is better for a person
to protect himself.

267
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:55,226
What does it say?

268
00:23:55,534 --> 00:23:56,296
I don't understand.

269
00:23:56,535 --> 00:23:57,798
What does it say?

270
00:23:58,037 --> 00:23:59,198
Let me see.

271
00:24:04,009 --> 00:24:05,568
What happened?

272
00:24:06,412 --> 00:24:07,641
The Japanese allow us

273
00:24:07,947 --> 00:24:09,005
to choose our nationality
in two years.

274
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:10,745
Those who don't want
to live under their rule

275
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:13,179
must move back to China

276
00:24:14,053 --> 00:24:16,181
or to wherever the foreigners are
in two years.

277
00:24:16,822 --> 00:24:18,017
Why does it happen?

278
00:24:18,257 --> 00:24:18,917
How come we have to leave?

279
00:24:19,158 --> 00:24:20,523
We get used to life here
but they want us to move.

280
00:24:20,759 --> 00:24:21,920
We have a life here.

281
00:24:22,661 --> 00:24:23,492
What should we do?

282
00:24:23,729 --> 00:24:24,628
Yeah.

283
00:24:24,863 --> 00:24:26,331
After taking over Taiwan,

284
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:28,932
based on the agreements of
the Treaty of Shimonoseki,

285
00:24:29,168 --> 00:24:30,158
Japan gave people in Taiwan
a chance

286
00:24:30,402 --> 00:24:32,393
to choose their nationalities.

287
00:24:32,805 --> 00:24:34,330
Those who did not want
to become Japanese citizens

288
00:24:34,573 --> 00:24:36,598
had to register within two years

289
00:24:36,842 --> 00:24:38,571
and leave Taiwan.

290
00:24:39,044 --> 00:24:41,103
When the deadline was up,

291
00:24:41,347 --> 00:24:42,576
people who registered to
leave Taiwan,

292
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:44,442
were more than 4500

293
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:48,017
which was only 0.16%
of the total population.

294
00:24:51,123 --> 00:24:53,956
Even though the Japanese government
issued Law 63

295
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:56,389
and established a colonial
ruling system in Taiwan

296
00:24:56,628 --> 00:24:58,392
under the lead of
Taiwan Governor-General,

297
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:00,928
Japanese and Taiwanese
living on this island

298
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:03,260
had to obey different sets of laws.

299
00:25:03,602 --> 00:25:05,969
The rights and benefits
of the Taiwanese

300
00:25:06,205 --> 00:25:07,695
were far less than those
of the Japanese.

301
00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:09,700
But most Taiwanese

302
00:25:09,942 --> 00:25:10,636
didn't want to abandon the homes

303
00:25:10,943 --> 00:25:13,241
which they have worked so hard
to build.

304
00:25:13,479 --> 00:25:14,913
Taiwanese have treated Taiwan
as a place

305
00:25:15,147 --> 00:25:17,377
where they can settle down.

306
00:25:46,311 --> 00:25:47,403
Your Excellency.

307
00:25:50,182 --> 00:25:51,377
Your Excellency.

308
00:25:53,352 --> 00:25:54,683
During the Qing administration,

309
00:25:54,987 --> 00:25:56,386
Taiwan did not have a police force.

310
00:25:56,622 --> 00:25:57,748
After the Japanese ruled Taiwan,

311
00:25:57,990 --> 00:25:59,924
they used policemen to
maintain social order

312
00:26:00,159 --> 00:26:02,150
and to carry out administrative orders.

313
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:05,462
The Japanese government gave
these policemen great power.

314
00:26:05,697 --> 00:26:07,426
What one did every day

315
00:26:07,666 --> 00:26:08,599
could be interfered by the policemen.

316
00:26:08,834 --> 00:26:09,926
Let me weigh that.

317
00:26:10,269 --> 00:26:12,931
Japanese police were very strict.

318
00:26:13,172 --> 00:26:15,504
Sometimes they exercised violence.

319
00:26:19,478 --> 00:26:20,343
A catty and a half.

320
00:26:22,848 --> 00:26:24,316
Your Excellency.

321
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:32,690
How much does that weigh?

322
00:26:34,193 --> 00:26:35,024
One catty.

323
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:36,819
Is that so?

324
00:26:37,229 --> 00:26:38,424
You bastard.

325
00:26:42,334 --> 00:26:43,961
What's your name?

326
00:26:46,839 --> 00:26:48,398
Chen Ching-Chung.

327
00:26:55,481 --> 00:26:56,710
At that time Japanese policemen

328
00:26:56,982 --> 00:26:57,949
used local hooligans

329
00:26:58,117 --> 00:27:00,176
as agents

330
00:27:00,452 --> 00:27:02,944
to abuse and harm Taiwanese.

331
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:06,280
So those working for the
Japanese were called

332
00:27:06,525 --> 00:27:08,789
"Three Legs" or Japanese lackeys.

333
00:27:30,782 --> 00:27:31,977
Seven to eight years

334
00:27:32,217 --> 00:27:33,651
after the Japanese rule,

335
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:36,387
local powers and leaders,

336
00:27:36,622 --> 00:27:38,351
in order to protect their profits,

337
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:41,059
began a long-term fight against
the Japanese

338
00:27:41,693 --> 00:27:43,661
and hid.

339
00:27:43,962 --> 00:27:45,020
The Japanese government issued

340
00:27:45,264 --> 00:27:47,961
the Gangster Penalty Order
to execute bandits.

341
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,827
It also offered favorable conditions

342
00:27:50,068 --> 00:27:51,126
to people who surrender.

343
00:27:51,370 --> 00:27:54,533
Then it waited for the right time
to counterattack.

344
00:27:57,309 --> 00:28:00,210
Chien Ta-Shih, Ko Tie-Hu
and Lin Shao-Mao,

345
00:28:00,445 --> 00:28:01,003
who later came to be known

346
00:28:01,246 --> 00:28:03,214
as the three great
anti-Japanese heroes,

347
00:28:03,448 --> 00:28:05,610
were exterminated one by one.

348
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:27,202
As for the gents and scholars,

349
00:28:27,439 --> 00:28:30,272
the Japanese government
tried to win their support

350
00:28:30,509 --> 00:28:33,308
so as to form
a new group of local leaders.

351
00:28:35,013 --> 00:28:35,980
In 1896,

352
00:28:36,215 --> 00:28:38,912
military policeman Takahashi
and CaptainTogo

353
00:28:39,084 --> 00:28:40,643
came to my house.

354
00:28:41,086 --> 00:28:42,815
I told them I was old

355
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:45,149
and sick to turn down the offer.

356
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:48,416
In the spring of 1897, I didn't expect

357
00:28:48,660 --> 00:28:51,288
Murakami Yoshio,
the prefect of Taichung county,

358
00:28:51,530 --> 00:28:52,827
would more than one time
send his interpreter

359
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:54,362
to see me.

360
00:28:55,634 --> 00:28:58,695
This time I didn't dare decline.

361
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:03,239
So that's how I became a counselor.

362
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:37,264
In order to profit more

363
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:39,500
from the colony of Taiwan,

364
00:29:39,745 --> 00:29:40,712
during the Japanese rule,

365
00:29:40,946 --> 00:29:43,711
the Japanese completed
several infrastructures

366
00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:46,178
At the end of 1895,
when Goto Shimpei was

367
00:29:46,418 --> 00:29:49,581
health consultant at the
Office of Governor-General,

368
00:29:49,821 --> 00:29:51,755
he hired Mr. Burton,
a British engineer,

369
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:55,392
to help construct tap water
and drainage systems.

370
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:57,186
Here and here

371
00:29:57,429 --> 00:29:58,123
This will supply fresh water

372
00:29:58,363 --> 00:30:00,991
for the people of the city.

373
00:30:02,601 --> 00:30:03,568
Good.

374
00:30:04,436 --> 00:30:06,268
How long will it take?

375
00:30:07,339 --> 00:30:08,738
It will take several years.

376
00:30:09,341 --> 00:30:11,969
It depends on whether
everything goes smoothly.

377
00:30:13,845 --> 00:30:14,573
Good...

378
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:15,746
In 1898,

379
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:18,211
the waterworks of Taipei
were completed.

380
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:21,647
Tap water officially entered
Taiwan's history.

381
00:30:26,725 --> 00:30:28,659
With that,

382
00:30:28,894 --> 00:30:30,328
Taiwan

383
00:30:30,562 --> 00:30:32,860
metamorphosed into
a modern society.

384
00:31:46,338 --> 00:31:47,669
In 1900,

385
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:49,169
Count Kodama Gentaro,
Taiwan Governor-General,

386
00:31:49,408 --> 00:31:52,537
held a conference on cultural issues.

387
00:31:52,778 --> 00:31:54,678
More than 150 provincial graduates

388
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:57,211
and tributary scholars
were invited to this event.

389
00:31:57,616 --> 00:32:00,916
I took a northbound train
from Hsinchu.

390
00:32:01,086 --> 00:32:02,144
It left at 9 o'clock

391
00:32:02,387 --> 00:32:04,185
and arrived at Tataocheng at 12.

392
00:32:04,556 --> 00:32:06,354
It was like magic

393
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:09,185
for the distance of
two places to be shortened.

394
00:32:09,661 --> 00:32:13,291
I guess with water and fire

395
00:32:13,532 --> 00:32:15,523
the train runs faster than the light.

396
00:32:16,001 --> 00:32:17,799
That should be what people mean.

397
00:32:22,507 --> 00:32:23,338
In 1900, the Office
of Taiwan Governor-General

398
00:32:23,575 --> 00:32:25,805
held a conference on cultural issues

399
00:32:26,044 --> 00:32:28,570
Wu Te-Kung and other scholars
took a train

400
00:32:28,814 --> 00:32:30,111
to visit the new armaments
and facilities

401
00:32:30,348 --> 00:32:33,613
the Japanese government constructed
in Taiwan.

402
00:32:37,155 --> 00:32:39,089
This is great.

403
00:32:39,324 --> 00:32:40,951
For the city of Taipei,

404
00:32:41,193 --> 00:32:43,184
This is very convenient

405
00:32:43,695 --> 00:32:44,992
Of course,

406
00:32:45,230 --> 00:32:47,221
For the Japanese Empire,

407
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:49,798
this is an outstanding achievement.

408
00:32:50,335 --> 00:32:52,702
I'm very happy.

409
00:33:00,946 --> 00:33:03,176
We visited a battleship
at the Keelung Harbor

410
00:33:03,415 --> 00:33:05,383
and saw the army performing drills.

411
00:33:05,617 --> 00:33:07,244
The machines at the sawmill

412
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:09,686
were as fast as lightening.

413
00:33:09,955 --> 00:33:14,654
The camphor plant
was also very advanced.

414
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:18,726
Camphor products are machine
packed like cigarettes,

415
00:33:18,964 --> 00:33:20,955
which saves a lot of time and energy.

416
00:33:21,199 --> 00:33:22,928
It was amazing.

417
00:33:23,268 --> 00:33:26,260
We also visited the electricity plant

418
00:33:26,505 --> 00:33:27,631
and the pharmaceutical plant,

419
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:32,304
demonstrating the wonders
of chemistry and physics.

420
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:38,074
The hospital trained doctors
and nurses,

421
00:33:38,316 --> 00:33:41,342
which set precedents.

422
00:33:49,194 --> 00:33:50,252
My daughter is getting married.

423
00:33:50,495 --> 00:33:50,825
I see.

424
00:33:51,062 --> 00:33:51,620
Congratulations...

425
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:52,955
Let me give you a discount.

426
00:33:53,131 --> 00:33:54,462
Thank you...

427
00:33:54,799 --> 00:33:55,789
In 1899,

428
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:58,059
The Bank of Taiwan was founded.

429
00:33:58,303 --> 00:34:00,795
Monetary law and currency reform
were carried out.

430
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:04,073
In the past, the Taiwanese
thought only coins made of

431
00:34:04,309 --> 00:34:06,607
precious metals
such as silver and bronze

432
00:34:06,845 --> 00:34:08,609
were of value.

433
00:34:08,947 --> 00:34:10,176
After the monetary system
was unified,

434
00:34:10,415 --> 00:34:11,905
they began to understand

435
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,640
the modern financial concept

436
00:34:13,952 --> 00:34:15,613
that paper money was
also value-based currency.

437
00:34:26,598 --> 00:34:27,326
During the Japanese administration,

438
00:34:27,566 --> 00:34:29,091
to develop agriculture in
Taiwan and industry in Japan

439
00:34:29,334 --> 00:34:30,631
was its economic policy.

440
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,003
In Taiwan new sugar plants
were constructed

441
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:35,138
to replace old sugar mills.

442
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:36,939
The tall chimneys
of new sugar plants

443
00:34:37,175 --> 00:34:39,007
became Taiwan's new landmarks.

444
00:34:39,844 --> 00:34:42,211
Taiwan's sugar industry flourished.

445
00:34:42,514 --> 00:34:44,676
During World War I,

446
00:34:44,983 --> 00:34:46,951
the production of beet sugar stopped
in Europe.

447
00:34:47,185 --> 00:34:49,677
As a result, Taiwan's sugar
sold not only in Asia,

448
00:34:49,988 --> 00:34:52,787
but also in Europe, America
and Australia.

449
00:34:53,024 --> 00:34:55,959
It was the golden time
of Taiwan's sugar industry.

450
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:04,095
Opium was gradually prohibited.

451
00:35:04,336 --> 00:35:07,362
It was not abolished until the 1930s.

452
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:12,771
Foot-binding and queues,

453
00:35:13,011 --> 00:35:15,241
however, were meant
to be abolished at once.

454
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,380
It, nevertheless, took several years

455
00:35:17,616 --> 00:35:19,209
for the practices to end.

456
00:36:25,617 --> 00:36:26,641
The abolishment of foot-binding

457
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:28,612
not only liberated the women
of Taiwan,

458
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:29,911
but also supply

459
00:36:30,121 --> 00:36:32,385
female workforce
for the Taiwanese society.

460
00:36:32,657 --> 00:36:33,590
This was the beginning
of a profound effect

461
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:36,294
on the emancipation
of Taiwanese women.

462
00:36:47,372 --> 00:36:48,533
In southern mountains of China,

463
00:36:48,773 --> 00:36:52,505
was born a holy ruler
and talented subject

464
00:36:52,777 --> 00:36:54,768
who has the ability
to rule a country,

465
00:36:55,013 --> 00:36:56,947
and the ambition to bring
peace to the country.

466
00:36:57,182 --> 00:36:59,549
He has his right-hand man
and faithful subjects,

467
00:36:59,784 --> 00:37:01,183
and the help of three religions

468
00:37:06,191 --> 00:37:07,556
(Buddhism, Confucianism,
and Taoism).

469
00:37:07,792 --> 00:37:09,351
Holy gods and Buddha
come to the world to preach.

470
00:37:10,128 --> 00:37:11,687
He has myriads of disciples

471
00:37:11,930 --> 00:37:13,523
and can do many things.

472
00:37:19,304 --> 00:37:21,068
The heavenly master comes.

473
00:37:21,673 --> 00:37:23,141
All the people should follow him.

474
00:37:25,343 --> 00:37:28,142
But as Taiwan
underwent modernization,

475
00:37:28,379 --> 00:37:29,744
an anti-Japanese rebellion
with religious coloring

476
00:37:29,981 --> 00:37:32,951
erupted in 1915:

477
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:36,415
the Xilai An Incident.

478
00:37:59,778 --> 00:38:01,974
Under the imperial decree of
the Taming Compassion State,

479
00:38:02,213 --> 00:38:05,274
I, Commander Yu,
will bring peace to Taiwan.

480
00:38:06,451 --> 00:38:08,180
In the 5th lunar month of 1915

481
00:38:08,419 --> 00:38:11,081
The Japanese have been
in Taiwan for 20 years,

482
00:38:12,457 --> 00:38:13,925
but their days are numbered.

483
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,260
Neither the heaven nor
the earth will tolerate them.

484
00:38:16,594 --> 00:38:17,925
Gods and men are in anger.

485
00:38:18,163 --> 00:38:18,925
Damn!...

486
00:38:19,164 --> 00:38:20,529
Damn!...

487
00:38:20,765 --> 00:38:22,426
Damn!...

488
00:38:22,667 --> 00:38:24,294
Damn!...

489
00:38:24,769 --> 00:38:28,569
I will rise up and fight on mandate
of the heaven.

490
00:38:28,807 --> 00:38:30,536
Yu Ching-Fang used folk religion

491
00:38:30,775 --> 00:38:32,004
to appeal to the people.

492
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:34,439
He declared that divine power
had appeared in Taiwan

493
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:36,977
and would establish
Taming Compassion State.

494
00:38:37,282 --> 00:38:38,647
His followers increased day by day,

495
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:40,748
which alarmed
the Japanese intelligence.

496
00:38:40,985 --> 00:38:43,454
The Japanese government
commanded to arrest

497
00:38:50,762 --> 00:38:51,558
Yu and his followers

498
00:38:51,796 --> 00:38:55,027
who retreated to Xilai An
(Xilai Temple),

499
00:38:55,266 --> 00:38:57,792
nowadays' Yujing and Nanshi
areas in Tainan.

500
00:38:58,036 --> 00:39:00,664
With traditional swords
and religious instruments,

501
00:39:00,905 --> 00:39:03,101
they fought modernized
Japanese troops.

502
00:39:06,377 --> 00:39:08,175
We regretted deeply.

503
00:39:08,546 --> 00:39:10,344
Furiously killing people,

504
00:39:11,049 --> 00:39:12,517
the Japanese

505
00:39:12,951 --> 00:39:14,385
lost their humanities.

506
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:16,585
Being protected by gods,

507
00:39:16,921 --> 00:39:18,446
I enforced justice
on behalf of the Heaven.

508
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:20,715
What did he say?

509
00:39:25,296 --> 00:39:26,058
Fire!

510
00:39:36,841 --> 00:39:37,933
The Xilai An Incident

511
00:39:38,176 --> 00:39:39,575
was the resistance of
the pre-modern people

512
00:39:39,811 --> 00:39:42,007
against a modernized police force.

513
00:39:42,847 --> 00:39:45,817
Then Japan had finished
the Meiji Restoration.

514
00:39:46,184 --> 00:39:47,549
The 1911 Revolution in China

515
00:39:47,785 --> 00:39:49,480
had also come to an end.

516
00:39:49,721 --> 00:39:50,279
Yet Yu and his party

517
00:39:50,521 --> 00:39:53,456
still imagined
a Boxer-type rebellion.

518
00:39:54,158 --> 00:39:55,387
Even though they fought heroically,

519
00:39:55,627 --> 00:39:57,356
their rebellion still ended in tragedy.

520
00:39:57,662 --> 00:39:59,255
The end of the Xilai An Incident

521
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:01,397
marked the end of

522
00:40:01,633 --> 00:40:03,067
armed anti-Japanese forces
in Taiwan.

523
00:40:03,301 --> 00:40:05,269
The new generation of Taiwanese

524
00:40:05,503 --> 00:40:06,766
who received Japan's
western-styled education

525
00:40:07,005 --> 00:40:09,133
launched political
and social movements

526
00:40:09,374 --> 00:40:12,571
that were quite different
in spirit and in contents.

527
00:40:41,172 --> 00:40:42,970
At the beginning of
the Japanese rule,

528
00:40:43,207 --> 00:40:46,268
the government resorted
to pacifying the aborigines

529
00:40:46,511 --> 00:40:48,479
and make investigations into
their forest resources,

530
00:40:48,713 --> 00:40:50,078
cultures, and customs

531
00:40:50,315 --> 00:40:52,545
of the areas they lived in.

532
00:40:52,784 --> 00:40:55,810
Only when Sakuma Samata
became the 5th Taiwan

533
00:40:56,054 --> 00:40:58,614
Governor-General, did the
aborigine suppression begin.

534
00:41:24,349 --> 00:41:26,477
With superior military backup,

535
00:41:26,718 --> 00:41:28,846
the Japanese moved
the Qing Empire's Detaining Line

536
00:41:29,087 --> 00:41:31,454
to the aboriginal territory.

537
00:41:31,689 --> 00:41:32,485
Some major sections

538
00:41:32,724 --> 00:41:34,658
even had electric barb wires

539
00:41:35,293 --> 00:41:37,728
to prevent aborigines from crossing.

540
00:41:38,363 --> 00:41:39,762
In 1910

541
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:40,487
when the Japanese government

542
00:41:40,732 --> 00:41:42,860
finished deploying the Detaining Line,

543
00:41:43,101 --> 00:41:46,230
they began armed attacks
on aborigine tribes.

544
00:41:55,013 --> 00:41:57,107
The aborigines could not
fight the armed Japanese.

545
00:41:57,348 --> 00:41:59,476
Anti-Japanese activities
were gradually quelled.

546
00:41:59,717 --> 00:42:01,378
In 1915,

547
00:42:01,619 --> 00:42:02,677
aborigine tribes in Taiwan,

548
00:42:02,954 --> 00:42:04,285
like the Han Chinese,

549
00:42:04,522 --> 00:42:07,719
were under the control of
the Japanese government.

